  "description": "Simulation role of a PhysicsBody. - `dynamic` — fully simulated (finite mass); moved by the solver once dynamics ship, and by `setTransform` meanwhile. - `static` — never moves; infinite mass. Ground, walls, level geometry. - `kinematic` — moved only by `setTransform` (game-driven); infinite mass, unaffected by contacts. Platforms, doors.",
